<div1 type="letter">

<note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
<note type="curatorial">0a</note>

<fw>University of Missouri<lb/>
Columbia<lb/>
Inter-Departmental Correspondence<lb/>
To:<lb/>
Subject</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>February 1, 1963</dateline>
<salute>Dear John:</salute></opener>
 
<p>It was a pleasure to write in support of your Fulbright application. Although 
it was the easiest recommendation I have been called on to write in a long 
time -- in that I had plenty of interesting things to mention, and giving a boost 
was anything but a problem -- I did not on that account slight the assignment. It 
was a good letter, because you are a good man. I have every confidence you'll 
get the assignment, and I hope you will arrange to go. It would be a big thing, 
wouldn't it.
</p>

<closer>
<salute>Sincerely, </salute>
<signed>Leon</signed>
<signed>Leon T. Dickinson</signed></closer>

<note>I sent it off arrived today</note>

<note>I thanked Dr. D. for this, and he said "O John it's
not a tenth of what I said in
the letter!" Jno.</note>


</div1>

